transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra at Score Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hi, my name is David Door. I got a prescription from you guys. I want to cancel it.

Speaker 1: I can help you with that.

Speaker 2: Could you provide me the phone number associated with the prescription, sir?

Speaker 1: Five seven three three three seven eight six six six.

Speaker 2: And lastly, just your date of birth, please.

Speaker 1: 12358.

Speaker 2: Thank you. All right, so the prescription here I see is for the 100 milligram Viagra written on December 14th by the doctor.

Speaker 1: Does that sound accurate?

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Okay, it looks like the doctor wrote it with refills.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Hey David, so not sure if you saw some initial notes from the doctor. You're not required or obligated to get this monthly.

Speaker 2: This is not a subscription. It's your prescription with refills that you can adjust to your needs if you would like.

Speaker 1: So if you wanted, I could simply just put an extended pause on this and then that would allow you to call in and place

Speaker 2: orders for refills as needed. It looks like you have about

Speaker 1: 10 refills here left on the script.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, I just canceled. I haven't taken anything to begin with.

Speaker 1: Gotcha, and I got 20 pills. So I got enough to last a little while.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right. Well, upon cancellation, it would close out the prescription altogether.

Speaker 2: What that means you might see some price increases in the future should you want to order again.

Speaker 1: There would be a significant delay in getting approved again.

Speaker 2: Just like the first time, just because you have to do the health survey and then have a doctor write you a new script.

Speaker 1: Gotcha.

Speaker 2: Hey David, I went ahead and did that for you and you're all set.

Speaker 1: All right. Thank you. Appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
